    "body": "## Problem statement\nThe mutation preflight selector already emits the complete ordered model-effort matrix and exact next response, but the repository-owned Codex user-visible response contract did not require that full executable output to be relayed at the mandatory visible stops. The visible response could therefore omit matrix evidence and surface only a status/recommendation summary.\n\n## Confirmed root cause\nThe missing control surface was the repository-owned response-layer contract in the Asynchronia plugin prompt and skill/routing instructions. Selector stdout itself was already complete. The validator and tests also focused on selector/core/CLI output rather than the user-visible relay contract.\n\n## Actual response-layer control surface changed\n- `plugins/asynchronia/.codex-plugin/plugin.json` `defaultPrompt`\n- `plugins/asynchronia/skills/model-selector/SKILL.md`\n- `plugins/asynchronia/skills/task-router/SKILL.md`\n- deterministic relay-contract validation and regressions in `plugins/asynchronia/response_relay_contract.py` and `tools/test_model_selector_response_contract.py`\n\n## Why selector stdout alone was insufficient\nChanging selector stdout or asserting only selector output would not repair the layer that tells Codex what must be shown to the user. The defect was that Codex could receive complete executable output and still present an incomplete visible response. This change binds the prompt/skill/router contract and validates that the visible relay must faithfully include the complete executable evidence.\n\n## Implementation summary\n- added explicit prompt and skill/router requirements to relay the complete executable selector output at `WAITING_FOR_INVENTORY_CONFIRMATION` and `WAITING_FOR_MODEL_SELECTION`\n- added deterministic response-contract validation for the ordered matrix, pair count, current state, and exact next response\n- added negative fixtures that fail on recommendation-only, omitted-pair, duplicated-pair, wrong-count, missing-state, missing-next-response, and prose-only relay shapes\n- synchronized repository plugin and marketplace versions from `1.0.14` to `1.0.15`\n\n## Regression strategy\nThe new regression layer targets the repository-owned response contract rather than selector stdout. It fails when the executable output is complete but the visible relay omits or distorts it, and passes only when the relay faithfully includes the authoritative evidence.\n\n## Version bump\n`1.0.14 -> 1.0.15`\n\n## Local validation\n- `python3 -m py_compile plugins/asynchronia/response_relay_contract.py plugins/asynchronia/model_selector_runtime.py tools/test_model_selector_response_contract.py tools/test_model_selector_full_regression.py tools/test_model_selector_snapshot.py tools/test_model_selector_runtime.py tools/validate-asynchronia-auto-model-preflight.py`\n- `python3 -m unittest tools.test_model_selector_response_contract`\n- `python3 -m unittest tools.test_model_selector_runtime tools.test_model_selector_snapshot tools.test_model_selector_full_regression tools.test_bridge_model_preflight tools.test_model_selector_response_contract`\n- `python3 -m unittest tools.test_model_selector_snapshot tools.test_bridge_model_preflight`\n- `python3 -m unittest tools.test_model_selector_runtime tools.test_model_selector_full_regression tools.test_model_selector_response_contract`\n- `python3 tools/validate-asynchronia-auto-model-preflight.py`\n\n## Scope exclusions\nNo changes to runtime, gameplay, UI, economy, persistence, NPC, battle, narrative, canon, Stage 6, workflow files, numbered bridge mailboxes, repository memory files, deployment mirrors, installed plugin cache, `main`, or PR `#231`.\n\n## Status notes\n- runtime smoke: `N/A_INFRASTRUCTURE_ONLY`\n- installation status: `INSTALLATION_DEFERRED_OUT_OF_SCOPE`\n- PR `#231` was reviewed only as negative historical evidence and was not used as the implementation base\n- this PR must not be merged until independent review is complete\n",
